@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #34495E
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontColor #34495E
skinparam RoundCorner 10
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #2E86AB
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #EAF2F8
skinparam ActivityFontColor #1B2631
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FDEBD0
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #E67E22
skinparam ActivityDiamondFontColor #1B2631
skinparam ActivityStartColor #2E86AB
skinparam ActivityEndColor #2E86AB
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FCF3CF
skinparam NoteBorderColor #D4AC0D
skinparam NoteFontColor #7D6608
skinparam ComponentBackgroundColor #EAF2F8
skinparam ComponentBorderColor #2E86AB
skinparam ComponentFontColor #1B2631
skinparam PackageBackgroundColor #F4F6F7
skinparam PackageBorderColor #7F8C8D
skinparam PackageFontColor #1B2631
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #D5F5E3
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #27AE60
skinparam DatabaseFontColor #145A32
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #F9E79F
skinparam ActorBorderColor #B7950B
skinparam NodeBackgroundColor #EBDEF0
skinparam NodeBorderColor #7D3C98
skinparam NodeFontColor #1B2631
skinparam RectangleBackgroundColor #EAF2F8
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #2E86AB
skinparam RectangleFontColor #1B2631
skinparam RectangleFontSize 13
skinparam TitleFontSize 18
skinparam TitleFontColor #1B2631

title Three Orthogonal Routing Axes (asked in order 1 -> 2 -> 3)

rectangle "AXIS 1 -- SCALE\n----\n**Question:** How big / automatable is this job?\n**Answered by:** /loop-which\n(7 sliders: size, independence, separation,\ncheckability, judgment, access/consequence,\npayoff-vs-setup)\n**Answers:** DON'T BOTHER / CHAT / ONE AGENT / AGENT TEAM\n**Decides:** how much of the stack engages at all" as Axis1 #EAF2F8

rectangle "AXIS 2 -- DEPENDENCIES (only if AGENT TEAM)\n----\n**Question:** Do units depend on each other?\n**Answered by:** the dependency graph in the plan/PRD\n**Answers:** flat (W=1) / dependent (W>1)\n**Decides:** one ringer manifest vs /loop-drive\ncompiling waves with gates" as Axis2 #FDEBD0

rectangle "AXIS 3 -- CHECKABILITY (asked PER UNIT, not per project)\n----\n**Question:** Is checking this unit's output\ncheaper than producing it?\n**Answered by:** whether an executable check exists\n(exit code, test, render, citation)\n**Answers:** checkable / judgment\n**Decides:** ringer task on a cheap engine vs\nstaying in the orchestrator's frontier judgment lane" as Axis3 #D5F5E3

Axis1 -down-> Axis2 : "2. asked next,\nonly if AGENT TEAM"
Axis2 -down-> Axis3 : "3. asked per unit"

note bottom of Axis3
  **Key insight:** Real PRDs are mixtures --
  Axis 3 routes each unit individually.
end note

@enduml
